From: Daniel Flanagan <daniel@lyte.dev>
Subject: [PATCH] scim migrations: allow required + common oauth2 attrs in create whitelist

The migration attr whitelist for OAuth2ResourceServer entries omits
oauth2_rs_origin_landing, which the schema declares as a MUST attribute --
making oauth2 client creation via SCIM migrations impossible
(AccessDenied when supplied, SchemaViolation(MissingMustAttribute) when
omitted). Also admits displayname and the common policy toggles
(strict redirect, localhost redirect, insecure-PKCE) so declarative
migrations reach parity with CLI-created clients.

--- a/server/lib/src/server/access/migration.rs
+++ b/server/lib/src/server/access/migration.rs
@@ -120,12 +120,17 @@
         ]);
         allow_attrs.extend([
             Attribute::Name,
+            Attribute::DisplayName,
             Attribute::Description,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsScopeMap,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsSupScopeMap,
+            Attribute::OAuth2RsOriginLanding,
+            Attribute::OAuth2StrictRedirectUri,
+            Attribute::OAuth2AllowLocalhostRedirect,
+            Attribute::OAuth2AllowInsecureClientDisablePkce,
             Attribute::OAuth2JwtLegacyCryptoEnable,
             Attribute::OAuth2PreferShortUsername,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsClaimMap,
             Attribute::OAuth2RsOrigin,
             Attribute::OAuth2ConsentPromptEnable,
         ])
     }
